      "id": 360713,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The Meerwein–Ponndorf–Verley reaction involves reduction of a ketone by treatment with an excess of aluminum triisopropoxide, [(CH<sub>3</sub>)<sub>2</sub>CHO]<sub>3</sub>Al. The mechanism of the process is closely related to the Cannizzaro reaction in that a hydride ion acts as a leaving group. Propose a mechanism.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbGNXIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--3406cb3a9057040bb8ce8e6af6915f606e5ab11d/OChem_19_EC_035.jpg\" alt=\"The reaction shows cyclohexanone with aluminum triisopropoxide, then hydronium ion to yield two products: cyclohexanol and acetone (three-carbon).\">",
